'''Calamarian''', also known as '''Mon Cal''', was a [[writing]] system used by the [[Mon Calamari]]. Some of the commands used on the [[MC85 Star Cruiser]] [[Raddus (MC85 Star Cruiser)|''Raddus'']] were in Calamarian. [[Resistance technician]] [[Rose Tico]] deciphered the writing to open the [[hangar]] bay doors, saving [[Resistance pilot]] [[Poe Dameron]].<ref name="Rose Knows" />

{{Language-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
Calamarian first appeared on a screen in the lead story ''[[Rose Knows]]'' part of [[Star Wars Adventures (2017) 6|sixth issue]] of [[Star Wars Adventures (2017)|Star Wars Adventures]]. The story was written by [[Delilah S. Dawson]] and illustrated by [[Derek Charm]].<ref name="Preview">{{IDW|url=product/star-wars-adventures-6|text=Star Wars Adventures #6}}</ref> In the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity, the [[Mon Calamari/Legends|Mon Calamari]] had a language called [[Mon Calamari (language)/Legends|Mon Calamarian]] which was both spoken and written. It was first mentioned in ''[[The Star Wars Sourcebook]]'', published [[1987]],<ref name="SWS">''[[The Star Wars Sourcebook]]''</ref> and first appeared in the [[1994]] novel [[Dark Apprentice (novel)|''Dark Apprentice'']].<ref name="Dark Apprentice">[[Dark Apprentice (novel)|''Dark Apprentice'']]</ref>

The ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' short story "[[Starlight: Shadows Remain]]," the first part of which was published in [[Star Wars Insider 207|''Star Wars Insider'' 207]]<ref name="Shadows Remain">{{InsiderCite|issue1=207|issue2=208|Starlight: Shadows Remain}}</ref> on [[December 14]], [[2021]],<ref name="Titan">{{TitanComics|url=insider/subscriptions|text=Star Wars Insider Subscription Information}}</ref> introduced the [[Mon Calamari (language)|Mon Calamari]] language.<ref name="Shadows Remain" /> Any connection between the language and the writing system has yet to be established.

